  "prompt": "Is there a maximum limit for a transaction via Net Banking through an SBI account?",
  "response": "Yes, State Bank of India (SBI) has transaction limits for Net Banking. The limits can vary depending on the type of transaction and the customer's account type. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. Fund Transfer Limits:\n- NEFT: Generally up to \u20b910 lakhs per transaction\n- RTGS: Minimum \u20b92 lakhs, no upper limit\n- IMPS: Usually up to \u20b92 lakhs per transaction\n\n2. Daily Transaction Limits:\n- Varies based on account type and customer profile\n- Typically ranges from \u20b95 lakhs to \u20b925 lakhs per day\n\n3. Payment Gateway Transactions:\n- Usually limited to \u20b910 lakhs per transaction\n\nPlease note:\n- These limits can be modified by the bank\n- Limits may differ for different types of accounts\n- Customers can request the bank to increase their transaction limits\n- Actual limits may vary, so it's best to check with SBI directly or through their Net Banking portal for the most current and accurate information specific to your account.\n\nFor precise and updated information, contact SBI customer service or visit a local branch.",
